The NSSA 2024-2025 Mentorship Program is back and better! 💪 If you haven't heard about it, it offers students in the Nutritional Sciences program an opportunity to connect with a professional in the same field of study. Mentees will meet up with their mentor based on their schedules, this is when you can ask them about literally ANYTHING (career advice, study tips, their personal experience, etc) By the end of the program, not only will you be more confident in your decisions for the future, you will also have gained valuable insights and made connections with your mentor! Who would miss out on a win-win situation like that?! ;)

Deadline: August 21st

Application Form: https://forms.gle/EVPuqr38oMUDsGeL9

Program Website: https://nutrisci.med.utoronto.ca/mentorship-program

The OISE Graduate Students’ Association is excited to extend an invitation to all OISE students to participate in one or more of our standing committees. These committees provide an opportunity for students to actively contribute to various aspects of GSA governance, helping shape the future of our graduate community. 

The collective purpose of these committees is to foster an inclusive, equitable, and sustainable environment for all graduate students at OISE. Whether you are passionate about accessibility, equity, finance, or sustainability, your involvement will be instrumental in driving positive change and ensuring that our community thrives.

Please complete the form Google Form in our bio to indicate which committee(s) you would like to be part of. This applies for members who wish to continue serving in the 2024-2025 academic year. The deadline is September 30, 2024. You can join more than one committee!

The OISE Graduate Student Research Conference (GSRC) provides a special opportunity for OISE students to present their research work in a familiar and collegial setting thereby contributing to their scholarly activities.

We are looking for at least three students to co-chair the OISE GSRC 2025. Co-chairs should have experience in organizing conferences to help in coordinating this very special event. We have set aside funds to pay $500 to each co-chair to collaboratively organize the event along with the support and input of the OISE Graduate Students’ Association and OISE Associate Dean, programs portfolio staff.
 
Individuals interested in co-chairing together are welcome to submit a joint application. Selection criteria will be based on the qualifications of the candidates and the quality of the concept proposed for the conference.

You can find more information on an email sent via the OISE GSA listserv sent to your email by the VP Academic on July 31st. Please send your expression of interest(s), conference vision, and your CV(s) to academic.gsa@utoronto.ca by Friday, August 16, 2024 @ 23:59 EST.

Opportunity Alert 🚨

Hey OISE students! @visionsofscience has an exciting internship opportunity available this Fall! 

This opportunity allows you to enhance your leadership, facilitation, and research skills while working directly with educators and students in professional development and STEM workshop settings.

The internship term will commence on September 9th and end on November 25th. The application deadline is August 30th! Scan the QR code from this post, or visit our LinkTree to apply now!

Dear incoming students,

Welcome to the University of Toronto, we are so excited to have you join the program! 

As you may already know, your Nursing Undergraduate Society (NUS) is organizing an orientation event for you; all information about this event is found in the post above, as well as in the description below.

September 4 will be the first day of your orientation. On this day, we will host a variety of fun events (with prizes of course!!), host a photo booth, hand out swag bags, take some time to introduce the NUS team, and have some light snacks for all of you guys to enjoy! This day will begin at 10 am, end at 6 pm, and take place in the Health Sciences Building (155 College Street). 

September 5 will be the next day of of orientation. On this day, we will provide everyone with a pizza lunch, and host a variety of fun lawn games! This day will begin at 12 pm and end at 4 pm. We will meet up in High Park (more information on specific location to come later). 

This orientation event is an amazing opportunity to meet your fellow classmates and make amazing memories that will stay dear to you forever. To join us, purchase a ticket (link in our bio!) until August 19, 2024 at 11:59 pm. 

Feel free to DM us if you have any questions!
